column1:
I would recommend incorporating more engaging teaching methods to make the course more dynamic and interactive. For instance, integrating group discussions, hands-on activities, or real-world examples could enhance student interest and participation.

Regarding assessments, it would be helpful to adopt a more inclusive quiz format that caters to different learning styles. Providing written copies of the questions alongside verbal instructions or allowing a slightly extended time limit could create a fairer and less stressful environment for all students.
column3: What u deeply appreciate about his teaching is his unwavering commitment to punctuality and consistency, as he has never missed class. This reliability creates a sense of discipline and respect in the learning environment. Additionally, his use if visual aids and well - structure presentations enhances the teaching process.
column5:
One aspect of his teaching that I found challenging was the lack of engagement during class. At times, it felt like we were merely fulfilling our roles as students and teacher, rather than genuinely immersing ourselves in the learning process. Admittedly, part of this may be my own responsibility, but I believe that Sir Arip also shares some accountability for making the class less stimulating.

Additionally, I struggled with his quiz format, which involved reading questions aloud twice with a strict time limit. This approach often felt rushed and made it difficult for me, as someone who processes information better through reading than listening, to perform at my best. I believe this style of assessment may have posed similar challenges for my peers as well. A more balanced or inclusive approach to quizzes could help accommodate different learning and comprehension styles.  I truly hope sir arip would take this into consideration.
column7: I hope that [PROFESSOR] could be more approachable in his interactions with students. While I fully understand and respect the importance of maintaining professionalism and clear boundaries between professor and students, it would be beneficial if he occasionally adopted a more relaxed and open demeanor. This small adjustment could help foster a stronger connection with his students and create a more comfortable and supportive learning environment
